comments.content:
@quadibloc - "I am full of obsolete inventions."  
Tell me about it. I spent years developing a perspective-drawing machine, just when the PC started becoming popular and could draw such scenes. In other cases I would get an idea, jot a few pages of notes and go to the next thing. One such idea of 1983 was for super-resolved microscopy using time-resolved florescence. The idea, but not me, got the 2014 Nobel prize in chemistry!

As to protruding letters these days most modern Arabic fonts redesign the ra ر to descend vertically downwards and not cause trouble conflicting with the next letter ريا I had to spend months learning how to use OT features to adjust the dots of the next letter but did not change the ra shape.
